cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with estimating the pose of a camera from a single image. The use of Deep Learning also suggests that it could be classified under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of stereo cameras and visual SLAM, which are commonly used in Robotics (cs.RO). The use of geometric algorithms for pose estimation suggests that it could also be classified under Geometry (cs.GR). Finally, the potential applications in VR/AR suggest that it could also be classified under Machine Learning (cs.LG).
